post_text:
Encuesta de Plan de Responsabilidad de Control Local (LCAP)
Cada año, los distritos de todo el estado deben revisar y actualizar su Plan de Responsabilidad de Control Local (LCAP). Parte de este proceso requiere buscar aportes de los interesados. Se han realizado varias reuniones públicas en parte del Distrito para obtener aportes de varios grupos, pero se está buscando aportes adicionales a través de la administración de la encuesta adjunta. Esta encuesta está disponible para el personal, los estudiantes, los miembros de la comunidad y los padres.
Esta encuesta sólo toma 5-10 minutos para completar así que esperamos que se tome el tiempo y darnos su opinión. Se valora y se utilizará durante el desarrollo del LCAP 2020-2021.
Tome la encuesta LCAP ahora:
https://forms.gle/SY6nFisePfofkPib8

post_text:
Local Control and Accountability Plan Survey

Each year districts throughout the state are required to review and update their Local Control Accountability Plan (LCAP). Part of this process requires seeking stakeholder input. There have been several public meetings held in Dinuba Unified to gain input from various groups but additional input is being sought through the administration of the attached survey. This survey will be made available to staff, students, community members, and parents.

It should only take 5-10 minutes minutes to complete so we hope you will take the time and give us your input. It is valued and will be used during the development of the 2020-2021 LCAP.

Take the LCAP Survey Now:
https://forms.gle/d9G8LQYvs4ecEtPK8

post_text:
Some information about Jefferson Elementary and concerns raised by parents concerning the temperature in the cafeteria......

Jefferson was modernized 6 years ago. A new
Wing of classrooms was added including a new library. All of the bathrooms were remodeled and all the plumbing infrastructure was replaced.

Currently, the state of California has no modernization funds available.

The district will be providing coolers until the weather cools a bit and will consider conducting an engineering study to see the feasibility of AC being installed in the near future.

post_text:
New School Year, New Boundaries.
We are looking forward to the start of school on August 10, 2017.
Following community meetings at our elementary school sites and public comment sessions in the spring of this year, Dinuba Unified established a new set of attendance boundaries for our elementary schools. This action was needed to bring our school sites in line with school site capacities. Parents of affected students received a letter informing them of their new schools. While initial enrollment numbers show a small number of grade levels with large class sizes, as in previous years, we use the first 10 days of school to balance classroom sizes. We will adjust class sizes so they fall within established contract levels.
We are looking forward to seeing you on August 10th for another great school year!
Follow us on Facebook to keep up on the latest Dinuba Unified School District news.

post_text:
Dinuba Unified is Holding Public Meetings for Community and Parent Input on Update to Elementary Boundaries

Dinuba Unified School District will be considering changes to school attendance boundaries to address overcrowding at several school sites. This change will affect the attendance boundaries of all Dinuba Unified elementary schools. Over the next month the District will be hosting information meetings at each elementary school to solicit input and comment on the two proposed attendance boundary maps. MAP and FAQ Information may be found on the district website.
https://goo.gl/IOyzo0

Tuesday, January 17, Wilson Public Meeting, 7pm
Wednesday, January 18, Jefferson Public Meeting, 5pm
Monday, February 6, Lincoln Public Meeting, 6pm
Tuesday, February 7, Grand View Public Meeting, 5pm
Wednesday, February 8, Roosevelt Public Meeting, 6pm
Wednesday, February 15, Kennedy Public Meeting, 5pm
